23 F. A school district may issue an alternate diploma to a
24 student who meets the definition of a student with the most
Req. No. 3962 Page 15

1 sign ificant cognitive disabilities and who participates in the
2 Oklahoma Alternate Assessment Program (OAAP) beginning in the 2023-
3 2024 school year. An alternate diploma shall be standards-based,
4 aligned with requirements for a standard diploma, and obtained by
5 the school year in which a student turns twenty-two (22) years of
6 age.
7 F. G. An alternate diploma shall not terminate a Free and
8 Appropriate Public Education (FAPE) for students with an
9 Individualized Education Program (IEP) unless they reach the maximum
10 age of FAPE. The IEP team shall determine subsequent courses and
11 services for students who receive an alternate diploma.
12 G. H. Students participating in the OAAP shall not be precluded
13 from attempting to meet the requirements of a standard diploma, and
14 participation in the OAAP shall not determine a student’s
15 educational setting under the Individuals with Disabilities
16 Education Act (IDEA).
17 H. I. Students who meet requirements for an alternate diploma
18 may count as having received a standard diploma for purposes of
19 calculating and reporting the adjusted cohort graduation rate (ACGR)
20 calculated pursuant to Section 3-151.1 of this title.
21 I. J. A student may be awarded an alternate diploma upon
22 completion of the following curriculum units or sets of competencies
23 at the secondary level:
